  icon: {fileID: 0}
  title: UI System
  sections:
  - heading: 
    text: The UISystem [Assets/MSPlayground/Core/UI/UISystem.cs] is used to spawn
      and manage prefabs of PanelModels [Assets/MSPlayground/Core/UI/PanelModel.cs].
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: 'The UI System component currently supports:'
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "\u2022  Localized texts within prefabs using the Unity Localization package"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "\u2022  Spawning complex panels with multiple localization keys used within
      one prefab (\u201CComplex panels\u201D are configured within a .json file in
      the Resources folder of the project. These configurations can be referenced
      by ID in C# scripts.)"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "\u2022  Spawning simple panels that populate a default prefab with a singular
      localization key"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "\u2022  Assigning Action callbacks to buttons within panels"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "\u2022  Initializing panels with a dictionary of {UnityEngine.Localization.SmartFormat.PersistentVariables.IVariable}
      objects so that localized texts within panels can be dynamically updated"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "\u2022  Despawning panels"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "\u2022  Overriding localized texts on certain platforms (Currently only
      supports the \u201Cvr\u201D override flag, but more overrides can be added
      in the UISystem Start() method with compiler flags such as VRBUILD)"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: Panel Model
    text: The Panel Model [Assets/MSPlayground/Core/UI/PanelModel.cs] is a JSON serializable
      model class for spawning complex panels.
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "\u2022  Data Model (Field Name / Json Property Name / Type / Description)"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "\u2022  ID / id / string / Identifier"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "\u2022  PrefabPath / prefab / string / Path to the prefab to use relative
      to Resources/Prefabs/UI Panels/"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "\u2022  PlatformOverrideKeys / override / Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string,string>>
      / A dictionary of localization keys to override given a platform flag. (e.g.
      \u201Cvr\u201D)"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "\u2022  LocalizationKeys / N/A / Dictionary<string,string> / Any other
      JSON property aside from the listed properties above are loaded  into the LocalizationKeys
      dictionary at runtime. The key names are arbitrary."
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: Example
    text: "ComplexPanels.json with 1 PanelModel. The model has localized texts (keys:
      \u201Ctext\u201D, \u201Cyes\u201D, \u201Cno\u201D) using the prefab \u201Cdialog_prompt\u201D,
      and the \u201Ctext\u201D key is overridden with another localization key on
      platform override \u201Cvr\u201D."
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: '['
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: '{'
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "  \u201Cid\u201D: \u201Ctest_platform_override\u201D,"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "  \u201Cyes\u201D: \u201CUI/yes\u201D,"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "  \u201Cno\u201D: \u201CUI/no\u201D,"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "  \u201Ctext\u201D: \u201Ctutorial/test_override_default\u201D,"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: "  \u201Cprefab\u201D: \u201Cdialog_prompt\u201D,"
    linkText: 
